# ── Bug contrast boxes ─────────────────────────────────────────────
bugs: COMMON BUGS — What Goes Wrong {
  style: {
    fill: "#1a0000"
    stroke: "#e74c3c"
    stroke-width: 3
    stroke-dash: 4
    border-radius: 6
    font-color: "#e74c3c"
    bold: true
    font-size: 13
  }
  bug1: |md
    **🐛 BUG: Return `0` instead of `-ERESTARTSYS`**
    c
    // WRONG:
    if (wait_event_interruptible(...))
        return 0;  // ← looks like EOF!
    
    **Effect:** `read()` returns 0 → userspace thinks file ended (EOF).
    Signal handler still runs. Process confused about read state.
    `cat` exits silently printing nothing. Data lost.
  | {
    style: {
      fill: "#2d0000"
      stroke: "#e74c3c"
      font-size: 12
    }
  }
  bug2: |md
    **🐛 WORSE BUG: Use `wait_event` (not `_interruptible`)**
    c
    // CATASTROPHICALLY WRONG:
    wait_event(mydevice_read_queue,   // ← TASK_UNINTERRUPTIBLE
               buffer_data_len > 0);
    
    **Effect:** Process enters **D state** (uninterruptible sleep).
    SIGKILL is **ignored**. Process cannot be killed.
    Machine may require reboot if many such processes accumulate.
    Visible in `ps aux` as state `D`.
  | {
    style: {
      fill: "#2d0000"
      stroke: "#8b0000"
      font-size: 12
    }
  }
  bug3: |md
    **🐛 SUBTLE BUG: Convert to `-EINTR` before returning**
    c
    // WRONG:
    if (wait_event_interruptible(...))
        return -EINTR;  // ← bypasses SA_RESTART!
    
    **Effect:** Programs using `SA_RESTART` expect transparent restart.
    Returning `-EINTR` bypasses the restart mechanism entirely.
    Every signal causes a visible `EINTR` even with `SA_RESTART` set.
  | {
    style: {
      fill: "#2d0a00"
      stroke: "#e67e22"
      font-size: 12
    }
  }
}
# ── Correct code reference ──────────────────────────────────────────
correct_code: CORRECT Implementation {
  style: {
    fill: "#001a00"
    stroke: "#2ecc71"
    stroke-width: 2
    border-radius: 6
    font-color: "#2ecc71"
    bold: true
    font-size: 13
  }
  code: |go
    static ssize_t mydevice_read(...) {
        /* Step 1: sleep OUTSIDE mutex */
        if (wait_event_interruptible(
                mydevice_read_queue,
                buffer_data_len > 0))
            return -ERESTARTSYS;  /* ← CORRECT: propagate immediately */
        /* Step 2: acquire mutex AFTER waking */
        if (mutex_lock_interruptible(&mydevice_mutex))
            return -ERESTARTSYS;  /* ← CORRECT: propagate here too */
        /* Step 3: recheck condition under mutex */
        if (buffer_data_len == 0) {
            mutex_unlock(&mydevice_mutex);
            return -EAGAIN;
        }
        /* ... copy data, unlock ... */
    }
  | {
    style: {
      fill: "#001a00"
      stroke: "#27ae60"
      font-size: 11
    }
  }
}
